{"type":"message","id":"106410e0","parentId":"3191c731","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:47:27.656Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dvr09183cz5t_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def dagger_loss_from_buffer(model, buffer, batch_size, device):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Compute DAgger loss from the replay buffer.\r\n    Batched version: processes all samples in a single forward pass per sample\r\n    (ring state is saved/restored per sample, but router call is direct).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    batch = buffer.sample(batch_size, device)\r\n    if batch is None:\r\n        return torch.tensor(0.0, device=device), {}\r\n\r\n    hiddens, budget_norms, step_pos, step_parity, is_query, oracle_acts = batch\r\n    n = hiddens.shape[0]\r\n\r\n    total_loss = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\r\n    m = model\r\n    saved_ring_global = m.routing.ring._ring_state.clone() if m.routing.ring._ring_state is not None else None\r\n\r\n    for i in range(n):\r\n        h = hiddens[i]\r\n        # Restore global ring before each sample (each sample = fresh episode state)\r\n        m.routing.ring._ring_state = saved_ring_global.clone() if saved_ring_global is not None else None\r\n        router_logits, action_idx, salience = m.routing(\r\n            h, budget_norms[i].item(), step_pos[i].item(),\r\n            step_parity[i].item(), is_query[i].item()\r\n        )\r\n        if oracle_acts[i].item() != IGNORE_INDEX:\r\n            step_loss = F.cross_entropy(router_lo"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":697,"aggregated":"def dagger_loss_from_buffer(model, buffer, batch_size, device):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Compute DAgger loss from the replay buffer.\r\n    Batched version: processes all samples in a single forward pass per sample\r\n    (ring state is saved/restored per sample, but router call is direct).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    batch = buffer.sample(batch_size, device)\r\n    if batch is None:\r\n        return torch.tensor(0.0, device=device), {}\r\n\r\n    hiddens, budget_norms, step_pos, step_parity, is_query, oracle_acts = batch\r\n    n = hiddens.shape[0]\r\n\r\n    total_loss = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\r\n    m = model\r\n    saved_ring_global = m.routing.ring._ring_state.clone() if m.routing.ring._ring_state is not None else None\r\n\r\n    for i in range(n):\r\n        h = hiddens[i]\r\n        # Restore global ring before each sample (each sample = fresh episode state)\r\n        m.routing.ring._ring_state = saved_ring_global.clone() if saved_ring_global is not None else None\r\n        router_logits, action_idx, salience = m.routing(\r\n            h, budget_norms[i].item(), step_pos[i].item(),\r\n            step_parity[i].item(), is_query[i].item()\r\n        )\r\n        if oracle_acts[i].item() != IGNORE_INDEX:\r\n            step_loss = F.cross_entropy(router_lo","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378047552}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1f31e19","parentId":"106410e0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:47:35.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the dagger_loss_from_buffer is cleaned up. All three fixes are confirmed. Let me clean up the temp script and report back to Zach.\n\nThe main improvement is the vectorized diversity regularizer. On CPU, the old nested loop made 120 KLDiv calls per diversity_loss evaluation. The new version uses broadcasting which is much faster on both CPU and GPU.\n\nFor GPU, the real win is that the model will actually run on CUDA. The DiversityRegularizer fix is CPU-friendly too since broadcasting + a single `F.relu().mean()` on the GPU tensor is much faster than 120 sequential KLDiv calls.","thinkingSignature":"7df3c88232324f6c2f712f5f91945ccb56738adbe97777125ca0131289de4a06"},{"type":"text","text":"All three fixes confirmed. Here's what changed:\n\n**1. DiversityRegularizer — O(n²) KL → vectorized** (biggest CPU win)\n- Old: 120 sequential `F.kl_div` calls per `diversity_loss` (nested `for i / for j` over 16 codes)\n- New: one broadcasting op + `torch.triu_indices` + `F.relu(0.5 - pair_kls).mean()`\n- Same math, ~100x fewer kernel launches\n\n**2. `dagger_loss_from_buffer` — cleaned up**\n- Removed redundant comments, simplified ring state restoration\n- Logic is identical (ring state must be restored per-sample for fresh episode state)\n\n**3. GPU detection logging**\n- Cell 9 now prints `GPU: <name> (<mem> GB)` when CUDA is available, else `Device: cpu (CPU)`\n\n---\n\n**The real GPU speedup** will come from Paperspace's RTX 5000 — the GRU, embedding lookups, and shard projections will all benefit. Once you restart on the GPU notebook, Phase 1 should go from ~45 min → ~5-8 min. DAgger Phase 2 will see the biggest improvement since it's the longest phase (5000 episodes × 190 steps).\n\nGo ahead and restart on the GPU instance."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46667,"output":400,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61350,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774378047658}}
