{"type":"message","id":"c501db4e","parentId":"f9037939","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:08.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is saying the notebook is still using CPU and not GPU. Let me check the notebook to see what's happening with the GPU detection. The issue might be that the GPU isn't being detected properly, or that the model isn't being moved to CUDA.\n\nLet me first check if there's a GPU available on the Paperspace machine and then look at the notebook's device detection code.","thinkingSignature":"0ca45f4208e98c2e5b1b0d3f29ab3bec2d72d7a7423df3afa601c65acc42c3a1"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the current state of the notebook and also verify GPU detection logic:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfi2nfcnbufo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\nfor i, cell in enumerate(nb['cells']):\n    src = ''.join(cell['source'])\n    if 'DEVICE' in src and ('torch.device' in src or 'torch.cuda' in src):\n        print(f'Cell {i} device logic:')\n        for line in src.split('\\n'):\n            if any(k in line for k in ['DEVICE', 'cuda', 'GPU', 'torch.']):\n                print(f'  {line}')\n        print()\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":263,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":54383,"totalTokens":58935,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379580675}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f27c703","parentId":"c501db4e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:09.944Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bfi2nfcnbufo_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cell 1 device logic:\r\n  import torch.nn as nn\r\n  import torch.nn.functional as F\r\n  print('torch:', torch.__version__)\r\n  print('GPU available:', torch.cuda.is_available())\r\n  if torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n      print('GPU:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\r\n  DEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\r\n\r\nCell 9 device logic:\r\n  torch.manual_seed(DEEPSEED)\r\n  ).to(DEVICE)\r\n  if torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n      gpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)\r\n      gpu_mem = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\r\n      print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\r\n      print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1075,"aggregated":"Cell 1 device logic:\r\n  import torch.nn as nn\r\n  import torch.nn.functional as F\r\n  print('torch:', torch.__version__)\r\n  print('GPU available:', torch.cuda.is_available())\r\n  if torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n      print('GPU:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\r\n  DEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\r\n\r\nCell 9 device logic:\r\n  torch.manual_seed(DEEPSEED)\r\n  ).to(DEVICE)\r\n  if torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n      gpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)\r\n      gpu_mem = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\r\n      print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\r\n      print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379589845}}
{"type":"message","id":"b01b9055","parentId":"1f27c703","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:22.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! In Cell 9, the GPU detection and CPU print are separate — the `else` branch is missing. The code currently has:\n\n```python\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\nprint(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')\n```\n\nThis should be:\n```python\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\nelse:\n    print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')\n```\n\nBut actually looking at the output, the indentation looks weird. \n\nLet me check if the else was properly added. Actually, the output from Cell 9 shows:\n```\n  line 32:     print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\n  line 34:     print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')\n```\n\nThe lines are indented differently — line 32 has more indentation (inside the if), while line 34 has less indentation (outside the if, so it always prints). This means the `else` was NOT added correctly. But that said, the DEVICE is already set to CUDA if available in Cell 1, so the model would be on GPU anyway.\n\nThe real question is whether the notebook is actually detecting the GPU and running on it, since Zach said it's still using CPU. I need to check if the wandb run from earlier was the CPU version before my fixes, or if there's something else going on with how Paperspace is handling the GPU detection.\n\nLooking back at the original output, it clearly said `GPU available: False`, which means torch.cuda.is_available() is returning False on that machine. This could be a Paperspace issue — either the GPU isn't being passed through to the notebook environment, the CUDA toolkit wasn't installed properly, or there's a driver mismatch. Paperspace does support GPU notebooks, so I should help figure out why the GPU isn't visible to PyTorch.","thinkingSignature":"7386af11cd79d4bf817f77881968eadae95032493f14a06e077117951aed782a"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it — the `else` is missing in Cell 9's GPU logging. But more importantly: if `torch.cuda.is_available()` is returning `False` in the original run, that's a Paperspace environment issue, not a code issue. Let me check the current run's W&B and also verify the notebook's GPU cell:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cwud4si0rias_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\check_gpu_status.py","content":"import json\n\n# Check the full GPU cell (Cell 9) in the notebook\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\nfor i, cell in enumerate(nb['cells']):\n    src = ''.join(cell['source'])\n    if 'gpu_mem = torch.cuda.get_device_properties' in src:\n        print(f'=== Cell {i} (full source) ===')\n        print(src)\n        break"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44847,"output":643,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379589948}}
