{"type":"message","id":"f2603c7f","parentId":"e645e629","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:26.188Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p53tgix4bvvh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Cell 9 (full source) ===\r\nimport os\r\nimport wandb\r\n\r\nWANDB_KEY = \"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\"\r\nos.environ[\"WANDB_API_KEY\"] = WANDB_KEY\r\n\r\ntry:\r\n    wandb.init(project=\"srmoe\", name=\"srmoe-run\", dir=os.getcwd())\r\n    print(f\"Wandb initialized: {wandb.run.url}\")\r\nexcept Exception as e:\r\n    print(f\"Wandb init failed: {e}\")\r\n\r\nDEEPSEED = 42\r\nN_CODES = 16; RING_DIM = 16; N_PREFS = 32\r\nLAMBDA_DIV = 0.1; LAMBDA_MARGIN = 1.0\r\n\r\ntorch.manual_seed(DEEPSEED)\r\nmodel = ArchitectureB(\r\n    d_embed=64, hidden_dim=128, budget_B=55, budget_T=190,\r\n    write_threshold=0.5, embed_seed=DEEPSEED,\r\n    use_sr_moe=True, n_codes=N_CODES, ring_dim=RING_DIM, n_prefs=N_PREFS,\r\n    lambda_div=LAMBDA_DIV, tau_start=1.0, tau_end=0.01, anneal_steps=5000\r\n).to(DEVICE)\r\n\r\ntrainer = SRMoETrainer(model, lr=3e-3, lambda_route=1.0,\r\n    lambda_div=LAMBDA_DIV, lambda_margin=LAMBDA_MARGIN, margin_target=0.5)\r\n\r\nprint(f'Total params: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters()):,}')\r\nprint(f'SR-MoE routing params: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.routing.parameters()):,}')\r\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n    gpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)\r\n    gpu_mem = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\r\n    print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\r\nelse:\r\n    print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":672,"aggregated":"=== Cell 9 (full source) ===\r\nimport os\r\nimport wandb\r\n\r\nWANDB_KEY = \"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\"\r\nos.environ[\"WANDB_API_KEY\"] = WANDB_KEY\r\n\r\ntry:\r\n    wandb.init(project=\"srmoe\", name=\"srmoe-run\", dir=os.getcwd())\r\n    print(f\"Wandb initialized: {wandb.run.url}\")\r\nexcept Exception as e:\r\n    print(f\"Wandb init failed: {e}\")\r\n\r\nDEEPSEED = 42\r\nN_CODES = 16; RING_DIM = 16; N_PREFS = 32\r\nLAMBDA_DIV = 0.1; LAMBDA_MARGIN = 1.0\r\n\r\ntorch.manual_seed(DEEPSEED)\r\nmodel = ArchitectureB(\r\n    d_embed=64, hidden_dim=128, budget_B=55, budget_T=190,\r\n    write_threshold=0.5, embed_seed=DEEPSEED,\r\n    use_sr_moe=True, n_codes=N_CODES, ring_dim=RING_DIM, n_prefs=N_PREFS,\r\n    lambda_div=LAMBDA_DIV, tau_start=1.0, tau_end=0.01, anneal_steps=5000\r\n).to(DEVICE)\r\n\r\ntrainer = SRMoETrainer(model, lr=3e-3, lambda_route=1.0,\r\n    lambda_div=LAMBDA_DIV, lambda_margin=LAMBDA_MARGIN, margin_target=0.5)\r\n\r\nprint(f'Total params: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters()):,}')\r\nprint(f'SR-MoE routing params: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.routing.parameters()):,}')\r\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n    gpu_name = torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)\r\n    gpu_mem = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9\r\n    print(f'GPU: {gpu_name} ({gpu_mem:.1f} GB)')\r\nelse:\r\n    print(f'Device: {DEVICE} (CPU)')","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379606125}}
{"type":"message","id":"00572657","parentId":"f2603c7f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:13:38.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the `else` is correctly there. The issue is that `torch.cuda.is_available()` is returning `False` on the Paperspace machine. This is a runtime environment issue.\n\nLet me check if there's a new W&B run that Zach started. The W&B URL from the earlier run was `https://wandb.ai/asdev/srmoe/runs/p843ewbx`. Let me see if there's a new one.\n\nActually, let me think about why `torch.cuda.is_available()` would return `False` on Paperspace GPU notebooks:\n\n1. **No GPU in the runtime** — Some Paperspace notebook plans are CPU-only. The free 6-hour instances might be CPU-only by default, and you need to explicitly select a GPU instance type when creating the notebook.\n\n\n2. **CUDA not installed** — Even with GPU hardware, the CUDA toolkit might not be properly installed in the notebook environment.\n3. **Different kernel** — The notebook might be running on a different kernel or Docker container than expected.\n\nThe most likely culprit is that Zach spun up a CPU-only instance by mistake. Paperspace does offer free CPU instances alongside GPU options, so he probably selected the wrong plan when creating the notebook. I should recommend he check what instance type he's actually running on and switch to a GPU-enabled one if needed.","thinkingSignature":"72f0e24e709c83179e2d6086fc8c0e17e02b982b8cb0831bb587b8be8c6ab8ad"},{"type":"text","text":"The code looks correct — `else` is there. The problem is `torch.cuda.is_available()` returning `False` in the Paperspace environment. That's not a code bug, it's a runtime issue.\n\nMost likely cause: **the notebook was started as a CPU-only instance**, not a GPU instance. Paperspace free tier has CPU notebooks — you need to explicitly select a GPU runtime when spinning up the notebook.\n\nQuick check — can you run this in a Paperspace terminal and paste the output?\n\n```bash\nnvidia-smi\n```\n\nIf that says \"no NVIDIA,\" you launched a CPU notebook. You'll need to stop it and restart with GPU runtime (the free 6-hour A5000 or A1000 is GPU-eligible — just select it when creating the notebook).\n\nIf `nvidia-smi` shows a GPU but PyTorch still says `False`, then it's a CUDA driver/version mismatch and we'd need to `pip install torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121` (or match whatever CUDA version Paperspace has installed)."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46088,"output":490,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60861,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774379606190}}
