{"type":"message","id":"a555d5d3","parentId":"36f7261d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:15:29.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the wandb init is using a Jupyter callback that conflicts. The simplest fix is to:\n1. Upgrade wandb in the notebook: `!pip install wandb --upgrade`\n2. Or disable the wandb notebook integration by setting `wandb.init(anonymous='never')` or by setting environment variable `WANDB_DISABLE_GCODE=true`\n\nActually, the cleanest fix is to just upgrade wandb at the start of the cell:\n\n```python\nimport subprocess, sys\nsubprocess.run([sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', 'wandb', '--upgrade', '-q'], check=True)\n\n\n```\n\nLet me update the wandb cell to include the pip upgrade at the top.","thinkingSignature":"03d224533b23d91eb40a57aa8d294d8a5aeefd9b5a2373b2ad78ffdbe6588456"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_47cfgg6sn3tk_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb","old_string":"import os\nimport wandb\n\nWANDB_KEY = \"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\"","new_string":"import os, subprocess, sys\nsubprocess.run([sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', 'wandb', '--upgrade', '-q'], check=True)\n\nimport wandb\n\nWANDB_KEY = \"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\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46704,"output":371,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61358,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379721612}}
