{"type":"message","id":"1e677d21","parentId":"7e793955","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:18:53.636Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but the issue is the wandb callback registration happens in the Jupyter kernel at import time. Even if we install 0.16.0, the kernel might have already loaded 0.15.10 when the first `import wandb` happened.\n\nThe real issue: these callback errors happen AFTER the cell runs (in post_run_cell). This means the Jupyter kernel has already imported wandb with the broken callbacks. Simply installing a different version won't help if the kernel has already loaded the module.\n\nThe actual fix would require:\n1. Restarting the notebook kernel (to reload wandb cleanly)\n2. OR downgrading before the first import\n3. OR upgrading to exactly the version where this was fixed\n\n\n4. The upgrade from 0.15.10 to 0.16.0 should work since it's a minor version change, but the kernel restart is the real solution here to ensure the new version loads properly.","thinkingSignature":"d04683b000afebc9d9c55f773966f0821dece955e53c8733fb99cad240f46de5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pyu23ctkpzk8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -X utf8 C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_wandb_cell1.py 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51948,"output":242,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66473,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379927684}}
