{"type":"message","id":"6fa78e9b","parentId":"dd318a5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:19:06.619Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! So the current state of the notebook still has `wandb --quiet` (not `--upgrade`). So when I ran `fix_wandb.py` earlier, the edit didn't actually happen because the exact string didn't match. Let me check what the actual current state of Cell 1 is and fix it.\n\nWait, actually looking at the earlier verification:\n```\nCell 1 - torch.cuda.get_device_name (GPU detection): OK\n```\n\nBut the raw pip line shows `wandb --quiet`. The earlier verification was finding `torch.cuda.get_device_name` which IS in Cell 1. But the wandb version wasn't actually updated in Cell 1 because my fix_wandb.py script found the wrong pattern (it had `--quiet` not `--upgrade`).\n \nSo the real problem is that Cell 1 has the old `wandb --quiet` that installs the broken version, while Cell 9 has `--upgrade` which tries to fix it but the damage is already done by Cell 1's import. I need to update Cell 1 to use `--upgrade` instead.","thinkingSignature":"834efd5eb667acfcf2815b35d91a72e229f2b706f461ca49e31cd55a4266a6e5"},{"type":"text","text":"Cell 1 still has the old `wandb --quiet` — my fix script missed it. Let me fix it properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4oscq1219odi_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_wandb_cell1.py","content":"\"\"\"\nFix wandb in Cell 1: wandb --quiet -> wandb==0.16.0\nPin to 0.16.0 which has the fixed callback signatures\n\"\"\"\nimport json\n\nNOTEBOOK = r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb'\n\nwith open(NOTEBOOK, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\nfor cell in nb['cells']:\n    if cell.get('cell_type') != 'code':\n        continue\n    src = ''.join(cell['source'])\n    if 'pip' in src and 'install' in src and 'wandb' in src and 'numpy' in src and '--quiet' in src:\n        old = \"subprocess.run([sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', 'numpy', 'wandb', '--quiet'], check=True)\"\n        new = \"subprocess.run([sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', 'numpy', 'wandb==0.16.0', '-q'], check=True)\"\n        if old in src:\n            new_src = src.replace(old, new)\n            cell['source'] = [new_src]\n            print(f'Fixed Cell 1:')\n            print(f'  OLD: {old}')\n            print(f'  NEW: {new}')\n        break\n\nwith open(NOTEBOOK, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    json.dump(nb, f, indent=1, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint('Saved')\n\n# Verify\nwith open(NOTEBOOK, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb2 = json.load(f)\nfor cell in nb2['cells']:\n    src = ''.join(cell['source'])\n    if 'pip' in src and 'wandb' in src and 'numpy' in src:\n        for line in src.split('\\n'):\n            if 'pip' in line.lower():\n                print(f'Verify: {line}')"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52249,"output":720,"cacheRead":14283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67252,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379934549}}
